rest_of_day_open: I see myself working on more music and continuing to stay quarantined in my room. There's not much I can do outside of the house, but I do see the rest of it to be very positive. I'll work on some music I haven't completed yet and I'll try and find some more people I can mix and master for.
critical_positive: The conversation I had with my partner was very eye opening. My favorite part that worked well the most was the relationship advice that she gave me about staying with one person rather than talking to a bunch of people that essentially won't better you in the long run. I can definitely see myself talking to her again!
critical_negative: At one point on the video conversation, I cut out and my video cut off to the point where you could only see my shadow or silhouette. I could not see it on my end, but my video on her end stopped for a minute or two, but it corrected itself.

rest_of_day_open: I think it will mostly be spent at home, doing crafts, reading things on the internet, possibly online shopping, plenty of cooking and watching TV, maybe applying to some jobs. I'm currently taking a mental health break from work and looking forward to starting some new roles in mid-summer, so I'm not pressuring myself to be overly productive.
critical_positive: I thought my conversation partner was very good at asking questions in the conversation, which for a young man is a very promising trait. I'm not sure if he had prepared talking points or was just a nice person, but I appreciated the time he took to both talk about himself and to ask me questions he seemed sincerely interested in.
critical_negative: My conversation partner was very young (18 according to him), and I'm 30- we're at different life stages and maturity levels, so it was sometimes hard to find things to talk about. I found myself wondering a lot how I was coming across- if I seemed really old to him.
